
[Richmond, 15 June 1780. JHD, May 1780, 1827 edn., p. 48: The Speaker laid before the House a letter from the Governor, respecting the removal of the Convention troops in case of danger, and enclosing one from Col. Wood on the same subject. TJs letter has not been found; James Woods letter, enclosed, must have been that of this same day, delivered By Light Dragoon from Charlottesville.]
